Take any picture file
Open in GIMP
Make circular selection
Invert selection
Remove selection (might be necessary to bucketfill with black or white)
Turn removed/colored selection to alpha
Export as .png
Open new .png in GIMP
Crop Image to Content
Scale to at least 160x160px or any multitude of that
Export and overwrite old .png
Open with Inkscape
Create Circle with Elipse Tool
Set Position to 0,0 and Size to 160,160 or the multitude of resolution of the image
Turn off Fill
Turn on Stroke (color RGBA:00a4e3ff, width 4px times the multitude of resulution of the image)
Export as Lastname-160x160.png
If you used a multiple of 160x160px as resolution open new Lastname-160x160.png in GIMP and downscale to 160x160
Export and overwrite Lastname-160x160.png
